The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 Mumbai, Feb. 4: Leela Palace amp; Resorts will set up hotels in Udaipur, Chennai, Hyderabad and Pune, the group chairman, C.P. Krishnan Nair said today. The Udaipur hotel is under construction and will be completed next year. It is expected to cost Rs 65 crore. In Chennai, a 15-storey property will be built at a cost of Rs 320 crore. The Hyderabad unit will cost Rs 310 crore, while the Pune hotel will be built with an investment of Rs 160 crore. 

 New Delhi, Feb. 4: BSNL and MTNL may announce on Monday the Re 1 a minute STD rate for their fixed and mobile phone users under the One-India plan. MTNL and BSNL initially resisted the move. They are now understood to have agreed to the proposal. 

 Salem, Feb. 4: Prime Minister Manmohan Singh today said his government would consider expanding Salem Steel Plant and making it an integrated steel unit. The government may also set up a separate railway division at Salem.




